<Author>todebald
<Content>Fairly nice; and decent price Stayed there for 10 days on a business trip in september 07. Got a quiet room with some view over the sea (a bit far, but still...), which I recommend since the main road is particularly noisy. Room was fairly large, clean, with free internet access -somewhat unstable though. Bathroom was well equipped and clean as well. The bed was not really comfortable, though. Staff was polite and willing to help, at least for check-in. Breakfast was served on the ground floor since the lounge upstairs was being refurbished; and was disappointing. The restaurant has reasonable price; however the quality is so-so, and got sick one day after eating fish. Finally, the pool is nice as well; and access is free. Overall, considering the reasonable price, this hotel is an option to be considered. 
